The table stores all the media that has been deleted, similar to the ARCHIVE table s job for text. This is the table that makes image undeletion possible.

This is a temporary buffer for storage of page view information. Stores the page_id value of any pages that where visited in teh hc_id field. The PAGE table s page_counter field is periodically increased based on this.
Describes images and other uploaded files. However, the image description pages are stored like other pages.
Stores all the links to images. This is good for a variety of functions, from link caching in the output functions to the what links here page.
Stores interwiki prefixes with their targets.
Stores details of IP addresses and users who have been blocked from editing.

Table used for a few generic cache operations if not using Memcached.

Holds information about old revisions of images. It will be filled when one uploads a new version of image to the wiki.

Core of the wiki: each page has an entry here which identified it by title and contains some essential metadata. The text of the page itself is stored in table TEXT.
PAGELINKS contains page-to-page hyperlinks within the wiki. The target page may or may not exist, and due to renames and deletions may refer to different page records as time goes by.
Used for caching expensive grouped queries.
QUERYCACHETWO is used for caching expensive grouped queries that need two links ( for example double-redirects ).
Contains details of updates to cached special pages.
Contains details of the latest modifications done to the wiki. Used to generate the recent changes pages, related changes pages, watchlists, and the list of new pages.

TIMESTAMP(6) WITH TIME ZONE(13,6) not null

Contains for each page that is currently a redirect ( i.e., not for old revisions which are redirects ) the id of the source page, the target namespace number, and the target page title without namespace.

Holds metadata for every edit done to a page within the wiki. Every edit of a page creates a revision row, which holds information such as the user who made the edit, the time at which the edit was made, and a reference to the new wikitext in the TEXT table.
TIMESTAMP(6) WITH TIME ZONE(13,6) not null
The SEARCHINDEX table is used to provide full text searches. Those can only be done with the MyISAM table type and the TEXT table uses the InnoDb type to improve concurrency, so a copy iis required.
Contains a single row with some aggregate info no the state of the site.
TEMPLATELINKS contains for each current page inclusino the id of the host page, the namespace number of the included page, and its title without namespace.
Stores trackbacks from external sites - provides notification when someone links to one of the wiki s pages.
This table is a cache of interwiki transclusion.

Stores notifications of user talk changes, for the display of the you have new messages box.

Contains for each registered user his or her id, and for all the pages the user watches, the namespace number, the page title without namespace and a notification timestamp, used for page change notification.
